{"id":"mishma","term":"Mishma","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Hearing. (1.) One of the sons of Ishmael (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 25:14\">Gen. 25:14</a>), and founder of an Arab tribe.</p>\n<p>(2.) A Simeonite (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 4:25\">1 Chr. 4:25</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 4:26\">26</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Genesis 25:14","1 Chronicles 4:25","1 Chronicles 4:26"]}